Would not be easier to use the solution described here:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28697484/how-to-invoke-a-getter-method-by-its-name

new PropertyDescriptor(name,                obj.getClass()).getReadMethod().invoke(obj);

I tried to implement this solution because I agree would be better:

private Object getValueByMethod(final String name, final Object obj) throws GenericUncheckedException \{
	try \{
		return invokeMethod(name, obj);
	\} catch (final Exception e) \{
		throw new GenericUncheckedException(e, &quot;Error invoking the method&quot;);
	\}
\}

private final Object invokeMethod(final String name, final Object obj)
	        throws IllegalAccessException, NoSuchMethodException, InvocationTargetException, IntrospectionException \{
	final Method method = new PropertyDescriptor(name, obj.getClass()).getReadMethod();
	method.setAccessible(true);
	return method.invoke(obj);
\}

